Warrior of 35 Battle Scars</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usvenkawryfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Svenka Wryfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/19/01 3:20:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling Othmir?</span><hr size=1> I just started pulling Othmir today and have found it to be relatively easy after two trial runs.  At level 59, I am able to single pull the warriors everytime using Annul Magic.  On one of my frist tries, I figured I may as well pull shamen as well, but they tend to mess up the kite when they stop to cast spells at you; I don't think it's worth the hassle.<br>
<br>
My strategy is to pull from either the middle camp or the merchant camp and kite in between the two.  I pull with annul magic, and when the warrior is on its way to me, but out of range of the shaman in the camp, I root it using the level 4 root and also flux it with the SoTF.  The root is rarely resisted for me and tends to last for the full duration.<br>
<br>
As soon as the first warrior is rooted, I immediately pull another warrior using annul magic again, flux him, and root him as well.  Since the duration of root is only 48 seconds, I am almost always able to pull the fourth by the time the first root is wearing off.  If a root doesn't last for its full duration, I'll just stop and re-root it before I continue pulling.    Once all four have been aggroed, I simply wait for all the roots to wear off and then kite them as normal.  Two things you have to be careful of are not to root them in range of any shaman, or the shaman will rebuff them, and on the same token, don't kite too close to any of the camps as the same thing will happen.  Having a warrior re-SoWed mid-kite would just be no fun.<br>
<br>
The only thing I do differently while quadding Othmir (aside from pulling with annul magic) is that I purchase SoW potions instead of using my JBoots.  I figure there's no need to risk it and with the loot you'll be raking in from the Othmir, you'll easily make your money back from the potions, along with a load of experience.  I am able to make over a blue an hour at 59 doing them.<br>
<br>
I use Pillar of Flame when I kite them and I have very very little +mana equipment and I have never ran out of mana.  PoF usually lands for the full amount of damage and I rarely even have to harvest.<br>
<br>
I've never had to worry about the roaming shellfish collectors either... they are green to me, and have never aggroed even when my set of four has walked right over one.<br>
<br>
Hope this is helpful!<br>
<br>
Svenka Wryfyre<br>
